writeObject

private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream s)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Save the state of the CHashtable to a stream (i.e., serialize it).

Serial Data:
The capacity of the CHashtable (the length of the bucket array) is emitted (int), followed by the size of the CHashtable (the number of key-value mappings), followed by the key (Object) and value (Object) for each key-value mapping represented by the CHashtable The key-value mappings are emitted in no particular order.
Throws:
java.io.IOException
Serialized Fields

threshold

int threshold
The table is rehashed when its size exceeds this threshold. (The value of this field is (int)(capacity * loadFactor).)

 

loadFactor

The load factor for the hashtable.
